reports/fixed-vectors-in-llms.md:34:- *E-BERT* (Poerner, Waltinger, Schütze; Findings of EMNLP 2020, arXiv:1911.03681) [established]: the closest existing thing to a working "kernel plugin". Wikipedia2Vec entity vectors are mapped by a **single learned linear transformation** into BERT's wordpiece embedding space and used **as if they were wordpiece vectors**, with no further pretraining. Beats BERT and matches/beats ERNIE/KnowBERT on unsupervised QA (LAMA), relation classification, entity linking, and fixes a real failure mode (surface-form guessing: "Italian-sounding name ⇒ speaks Italian"). Key nuances: the host model was already trained; the entity vectors were *distributionally* trained (not formal/canonical); and a learned aligner was still required.
reports/architecture-and-poc-options.md:3:Research agent report, 2026-07-07. Programme: NSM-style kernel (~65 primes + explication molecules) with canonical **training-free** concept vectors integrated into LM/LCM architectures. Coordination: sparq-org/sparq#1683.
reports/architecture-and-poc-options.md:64:- **"Towards Universal Semantics with Large Language Models" (arXiv:2505.11764)** [established]: first NSM × LLM work — LLMs generating NSM explications. Not an architecture paper, but a ready-made pipeline precedent for *building* the kernel's explication data (and a citable bridge from Wierzbicka/Goddard's ~65 primes to NLP).
reports/architecture-and-poc-options.md:69:- **Training-free structure-derived vectors** (how to actually *make* kernel vectors without training a text model): graph/spectral embeddings of the explication graph; hyperbolic embeddings of hierarchies (Poincaré, arXiv:1705.08039); deterministic codebooks (Bit Cipher, arXiv:2311.11012) [established as techniques; their use for an NSM kernel is [speculative]/novel].
reports/architecture-and-poc-options.md:71:**Verdict**: searches for "frozen concept embeddings", "fixed semantic anchors", "training-free grounding tokens" surface adjacent work (above) but **no published attempt to build fixed, human-designed (NSM-style) concept coordinates into an LM's vocabulary** — positive or negative. The niche appears genuinely open [established, to the limit of several web searches]; the nearest result (2507.04886) is best read as a *pre-registered threat* to the hypothesis rather than support.
reports/architecture-and-poc-options.md:120:*Method*: tasks expressible in explications (entailment/paraphrase over NSM-explicable TinyStories-domain sentences, synthesised via the 2505.11764-style pipeline); finetune SmolLM2-135M (embeddings frozen, LoRA on attention; new concept rows initialised to kernel vectors and excluded from training via PEFT `trainable_token_indices` complement) under three input codings: text-only / text+concept-tokens / concept-tokens-only. Measure accuracy per input token and per training example. *Success*: concept-only ≥ text-only at ≤50% of the tokens. *Failure*: concept coding strictly worse at matched training → dense-I/O claim damaged. *Compute*: 6–12 GPU-h; **$5–15**.
